    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of porcelain made in China during the Ming dynasty (1368-1644) in the provinces of Fukien and Kwangtung, and supposedly shipped from the port of Swatow. The style is characterized by both blue-and-white and multicolored wares.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de la porcelana hecho en China durante la dinastía de Ming (1368-1644) en las provincias de Fukien y de Kwangtung, y supuestamente enviados del puerto de Swatow. El estilo es caracterizado por las objetos azul-y-blanco y multicolores.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van porselein dat in China werd gemaakt ten tijde van de Ming-dynastie (1368-1644) in de provincies Fukien en Kwangtung, en waarschijnlijk werd verscheept vanuit de haven van Shantou. De stijl wordt gekenmerkt door blauw-wit en veelkleurig aardewerk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用指中國明代（西元1368年至1644年）福建、廣東兩省的瓷器風格，可能由汕頭港輸至海外。該風格的瓷器有些為青白色，有些則為多色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
